profile_positions.description:
Program manager of "Physics of Devices"; 
Lecturing pre- and postgraduate courses;
Guidance of 4 - 5 Ph.D. students, plus postdocs and technicians (expansion to total 15 - 18 people);
Initiating and negotiating new projects (Akzo Nobel (since 1996);
Coordinating national and international networks;
Organizer and co-organizer of various international Conferences (Materials Research Society - MRS);
Promoting the industrial implementation of the research developments;
Multidisciplinary interaction with other scientific communities (e.g. organic semiconductors, semiconducting nanoparticle composites);
Maintain international relations (PV institutes in USA and institutes and companies in Japan). 
Involved in planning of future research fields in three departments; 
Chair of the Board of the Department of Atomic and Interface Physics
Authored the textbook “Amorphous and Microcrystalline Silicon Solar Cells: Modeling, Materials and Device Technology” (Kluwer Academic Publishers, 1998, ISBN 0-7923-8317-6).
